{"add":{"doc":{"id":"5c6275122ab728b6adad472c8a158fa3cf2a3e31c6ebf5ff79ec204c6511da1e","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Iggy-Pop_1977.jpg/220px-Iggy-Pop_1977.jpg","previous":[],"after":["After going through rehab, Pop embarked upon a successful solo career in 1976, beginning with the albums The Idiot and Lust for Life. Relocated to Los Angeles, California, Ron Asheton formed the short-lived band the New Order (not to be confused with the UK band New Order), with Stooges alumni Recca and Thurston. Ron Asheton later joined Destroy All Monsters. Williamson worked with Pop as a producer and engineer during his early solo career – the Kill City and New Values albums are a product of this collaboration – but began a long break from the music industry in 1980. Scott Asheton performed with Sonic's Rendezvous Band and the Scott Morgan Group. Dave Alexander died of pulmonary edema related to his pancreatitis in 1975."]}}}